SIMPLE: spiritless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spiritless
<hw>Spir"it*less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of
spirit; wanting animation; wanting cheerfulness; dejected;
depressed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute of vigor; wanting life, courage, or
fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A men so faint, so <qex>spiritless</qex>,⟦br⟧
So dull, so dead in lock, so woebegone.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having no breath; extinct; dead.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>spiritless</xex> body.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Greenhill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Spir"it*less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Spir"it*less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spiritoso</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
